  "title": "The Nosology of Genetic Disease",
  "abstract": "Syndromes associated with chromosomal anomalies can be identified unequivocally through karyotyping; with point mutations, the task of correct classification is more difficult. Concluding the series on medical genetics, Dr. McKusick points out that as subtle methods have been developed to differentiate phenotypically similar but genetically heterogeneous conditions, the number of discrete genetic entities has risen into the hundreds.",
